oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: McMillan Grocery Store in Bingham
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: General store in Bingham that was run by mother and son Mollie and Newt McMillan. They are pictured in front of the store.

Newton James McMillan (1897-1985) and Mollie Journey McMillan (1876-1966) were mother and son, and lived in Franklin. The McMillan family operated a thriving store at Hillsboro for the past twenty years. First going into the merchandising business when brothers Odie, Newt and Ellis McMillan opened the store known as McMillan Brothers at Forrest Home, which ran until the depression.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
